access_key.description:
The access key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

custom_ca_bundle.description: File containing custom root and intermediate certificates. Can also be configured using the `AWS_CA_BUNDLE` environment variable. (Setting `ca_bundle` in the shared config file is not supported.)

ec2_metadata_service_endpoint.description: Address of the EC2 metadata service endpoint to use. Can also be configured using the `AWS_EC2_METADATA_SERVICE_ENDPOINT` environment variable.

ec2_metadata_service_endpoint_mode.description: Protocol to use with EC2 metadata service endpoint.Valid values are `IPv4` and `IPv6`. Can also be configured using the `AWS_EC2_METADATA_SERVICE_ENDPOINT_MODE` environment variable.

http_proxy.description: URL of a proxy to use for HTTP requests when accessing the AWS API. Can also be set using the `HTTP_PROXY` or `http_proxy` environment variables.

https_proxy.description: URL of a proxy to use for HTTPS requests when accessing the AWS API. Can also be set using the `HTTPS_PROXY` or `https_proxy` environment variables.

insecure.description: Explicitly allow the provider to perform "insecure" SSL requests. If omitted, default value is `false`

max_retries.description:
The maximum number of times an AWS API request is
being executed. If the API request still fails, an error is
thrown.

no_proxy.description: Comma-separated list of hosts that should not use HTTP or HTTPS proxies. Can also be set using the `NO_PROXY` or `no_proxy` environment variables.

profile.description:
The profile for API operations. If not set, the default profile
created with `aws configure` will be used.

region.description:
The region where AWS operations will take place. Examples
are us-east-1, us-west-2, etc.

retry_mode.description: Specifies how retries are attempted. Valid values are `standard` and `adaptive`. Can also be configured using the `AWS_RETRY_MODE` environment variable.

s3_us_east_1_regional_endpoint.description: Specifies whether S3 API calls in the `us-east-1` region use the legacy global endpoint or a regional endpoint. Valid values are `legacy` or `regional`. Can also be configured using the `AWS_S3_US_EAST_1_REGIONAL_ENDPOINT` environment variable or the `s3_us_east_1_regional_endpoint` shared config file parameter

s3_use_path_style.description:
Set this to true to enable the request to use path-style addressing,
i.e., https://s3.amazonaws.com/BUCKET/KEY. By default, the S3 client will
use virtual hosted bucket addressing when possible
(https://BUCKET.s3.amazonaws.com/KEY). Specific to the Amazon S3 service.

secret_key.description:
The secret key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

shared_config_files.description: List of paths to shared config files. If not set, defaults to [~/.aws/config].

shared_credentials_files.description: List of paths to shared credentials files. If not set, defaults to [~/.aws/credentials].

skip_credentials_validation.description: Skip the credentials validation via STS API. Used for AWS API implementations that do not have STS available/implemented.

skip_metadata_api_check.description: Skip the AWS Metadata API check. Used for AWS API implementations that do not have a metadata api endpoint.

skip_region_validation.description: Skip static validation of region name. Used by users of alternative AWS-like APIs or users w/ access to regions that are not public (yet).

skip_requesting_account_id.description: Skip requesting the account ID. Used for AWS API implementations that do not have IAM/STS API and/or metadata API.

sts_region.description:
The region where AWS STS operations will take place. Examples
are us-east-1 and us-west-2.

token.description:
session token. A session token is only required if you are
using temporary security credentials.

token_bucket_rate_limiter_capacity.description: The capacity of the AWS SDK's token bucket rate limiter.

use_dualstack_endpoint.description: Resolve an endpoint with DualStack capability

use_fips_endpoint.description: Resolve an endpoint with FIPS capability

duration.description: The duration, between 15 minutes and 12 hours, of the role session. Valid time units are ns, us (or µs), ms, s, h, or m.

external_id.description: A unique identifier that might be required when you assume a role in another account.

policy.description: IAM Policy JSON describing further restricting permissions for the IAM Role being assumed.

policy_arns.description: Amazon Resource Names (ARNs) of IAM Policies describing further restricting permissions for the IAM Role being assumed.

role_arn.description: Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an IAM Role to assume prior to making API calls.

session_name.description: An identifier for the assumed role session.

source_identity.description: Source identity specified by the principal assuming the role.

transitive_tag_keys.description: Assume role session tag keys to pass to any subsequent sessions.

duration.description: The duration, between 15 minutes and 12 hours, of the role session. Valid time units are ns, us (or µs), ms, s, h, or m.

tags.description: Resource tags to default across all resources

block.description: Configuration block with settings to default resource tags across all resources.
